    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1)No of Pacific islanders or households covered by climate risk insurance products disaggregated by gender 
2) No of small businesses covered by climate risk insurance products</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2021">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">Presently no such products or services are available in the Pacific for the micro and meso level segments.</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1500- total number of beneficiaries (individuals and businesses) covered by market-based parametric insurance solutions</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Development and launch of Fiji&#x2019;s and the Pacific&#x2019;s first market-based parametric microinsurance products. The product was launched on August 25th by the Hon&#x2019;ble Attorney-General and Minister for Economy of the Fijian government. 
By then end of 2021, a total of 1388 beneficiaries had registered for the product of which 442 (32%) were women. Out of this, 1,248 had been issued certificates of insurance. 402 (32%) of these were women.

5 agri-agencies (CCSLA, FCML, FRL, SCGC, and TDFCAL) were onboarded in 2021 to provide climate risk insurance to their members. Besides two local private insurance companies offer the product in a co-insurance agreement. Total 12 performance based grant agreements signed.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
